setSelectedFile(null);\n    setUploadProgress(0);\n  };\n\n  // Validar formato e tamanho do arquivo\n  const validateFile = (file) => {\n    const allowedFormats = ['mp4', 'avi', 'mov', 'wmv', 'flv',         setUploading(false);\n                setUploadProgress(0);\n                resolve(result.filename);\n              }, 1000);\n            } catch (e) {\n              setUploading(false);\n              setUploadProgress(0);\n              reject(new Error('Erro ao processar resposta do servidor'));\n            }\n          } else {\n            try {\n              const errorResult = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText);\n              setUploading(false);\n              setUploadProgress(0);\n              reject(new Error(errorResult.error || 'Erro no upload'));\n            } catch (e) {\n              setUploading(false);\n              setUploadProgress(0);\n              reject(new Error(`Erro no upload: ${xhr.status} ${xhr.statusText}`));\n            }\n          }\n        });\n\n        xhr.addEventListener('error', () => {\n          setUploading(false);\n          setUploadProgress(0);\n          reject(new Error('Erro de conexão durante o upload'));\n        });\n\n
